<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="13277441">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>The second paramater to <code>usort</code> should be a function. See <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/function.usort.php">http://php.net/manual/en/function.usort.php</a>. You would need to pass it a function like:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">cmp</span>(<span class="hljs-params"><span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span></span>)
</span>{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">strcmp</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>-&gt;title, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>-&gt;title);
}
</code></pre>

<p>I think you would then call it like <code>usort($restrictedEvents, "cmp");</code>.</p>
    </div>
